      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
        "old_string": "## Admission and Context Integration\n\n- pkg/admission/audit.go: WithAudit() wraps admission handlers to log annotations into the audit event\n- pkg/endpoints/filters/request_deadline.go: WithRequestDeadline() handles audit for timeout-related errors\n\nThe audit system uses Go context to thread the AuditContext through the entire request pipeline, allowing any handler to access the current audit event via audit.AuditContextFrom() and audit.AuditEventFrom().\"",
        "new_string": "## Admission and Context Integration\n\n- pkg/admission/audit.go: WithAudit() wraps admission handlers to log annotations into the audit event\n- pkg/endpoints/filters/request_deadline.go: WithRequestDeadline() handles audit for timeout-related errors\n- pkg/endpoints/filters/authn_audit.go: WithFailedAuthenticationAudit() audits failed authentication attempts\n\n## API Scheme Registration\n\nThe audit system's API types are registered and made available through:\n- pkg/apis/audit/install/install.go: Registers audit API groups and versions with the scheme\n- pkg/apis/audit/register.go: Registers the internal audit API\n- pkg/apis/audit/v1/register.go: Registers the v1 audit API\n\nThe audit system uses Go context to thread the AuditContext through the entire request pipeline, allowing any handler to access the current audit event via audit.AuditContextFrom() and audit.AuditEventFrom(). Events are logged at multiple stages (RequestReceived, ResponseStarted, ResponseComplete) through the filter chain, with the Union backend pattern enabling simultaneous dispatch to log file and webhook backends.\"",
        "replace_all": false
